.TH "HTMLMediaElement.preservesPitch" "JS" "December 5, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLMediaElement.preservesPitch \- HTMLMediaElement: preservesPitch
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]HTMLMediaElement.preservesPitch\f[B]\f[R] property
determines whether or not the browser should adjust the pitch of the
audio to compensate for changes to the playback rate made by setting
\f[CR]HTMLMediaElement.playbackRate\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A boolean value defaulting to \f[CR]true\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Setting the preservesPitch property
In this example, we have an \f[CR]<audio>\f[R] element, a range control
that adjusts the playback rate, and a checkbox that sets
\f[CR]preservesPitch\f[R].
.PP
Try playing the audio, then adjusting the playback rate, then enabling
and disabling the checkbox.
.IP
.EX
<audio
  controls
  src=\[dq]https://mdn.github.io/webaudio\-examples/audio\-basics/outfoxing.mp3\[dq]></audio>

<div>
  <label for=\[dq]rate\[dq]>Adjust playback rate:</label>
  <input id=\[dq]rate\[dq] type=\[dq]range\[dq] min=\[dq]0.25\[dq] max=\[dq]3\[dq] step=\[dq]0.05\[dq] value=\[dq]1\[dq] />
</div>

<div>
  <label for=\[dq]pitch\[dq]>Preserve pitch:</label>
  <input type=\[dq]checkbox\[dq] id=\[dq]pitch\[dq] name=\[dq]pitch\[dq] checked />
</div>
.EE
.IP
.EX
const audio = document.querySelector(\[dq]audio\[dq]);
document.getElementById(\[dq]rate\[dq]).addEventListener(\[dq]change\[dq], (e) => {
  audio.playbackRate = e.target.value;
});
document.getElementById(\[dq]pitch\[dq]).addEventListener(\[dq]change\[dq], (e) => {
  audio.preservesPitch = e.target.checked;
});
.EE
